1.title: Moving Things
1.plot: De Li discovers a box she used to pick fruit from a tree has disappeared.

2.title: Showtime
2.plot: Lau Lau plans a show for which she has prepared a special dance, but her friends join in and spoil the performance.

3.title: Trumpet
3.plot: Yo Jojo and Nok Tok make noise with a hollow branch, but the sound scares Lau Lau's narabug.

4.title: Strawberries
4.plot: De Li finds a lovely strawberry patch but, after she goes to Yogo, she can't find the patch again!

5.title: Snuggly Nest
5.plot: The friends discover a bird has made a nest out of a cushion.

6.title: Whistle
6.plot: When Nok Tok discovers he cannot whistle, Lau Lau advises him to practice. However, he decides to use his Anything Machine instead.

7.title: Shy Flower
7.plot: De Li has a large plant in her garden that won't open its flower. She tries putting it in the sun and watering it but it won't flower. Eventually she works out it flowers by stroking it. It produces lots of seeds and soon the flowers are everywhere.

8.title: Going Bananas
8.plot: Lau Lau paints pictures of bananas, but Yojojo wants to eat them.

9.title: Nok Tok's Naracar
9.plot: Nok Tok builds a car in order to help De Li, Yojojo and Lau Lau lift and carry things.

10.title: Bubble
10.plot: A beautiful bubble floats past Yojojo's home, and he chases after it to stop it bursting.

11.title: Nok Tok's Happy Plant
11.plot: When his new plant starts to go droopy, Nok Tok has to admit he was wrong and accept that his friends were right all along.

12.title: Counting Seeds
12.plot: De Li has some beautiful jiggly seeds which will grow into cabbages. She wants to know how many there are - but she keeps losing count.

13.title: Being Brave
13.plot: Yo Jojo plays happily with his narabug in De Li's garden but the narabug disappears and a big scary shape appears on the side of De Li's garden shed!

14.title: Catch
14.plot: The Piplings decide to play with it together but, much to Nok Tok's dismay, he discovers that he can't catch as well as the other Piplings.

15.title: Nok Tok Thinks Big
15.plot: When Nok Tok accidentally destroys De Li's sand castle, he vows to replace it with a bigger, more splendid one.

16.title: Tricky Kicky
16.plot: The Piplings are playing Tricky Kicky but De Li hasn't got the confidence to play without a lucky pebble.

17.title: Green Mango
17.plot: Yo Jojo eats some delicious mango. But all the other mangoes he finds aren't ripe yet.

18.title: Songbird
18.plot: Yo Jojo finds a bird and they sing together beautifully. But it soon stops singing.

19.title: Fruity Fun
19.plot: Nok Tok tried to divide his fir cones from his Anything Machine with Lau Lau.

20.title: Hiccups
20.plot: Yo Jojo has perfected his triple spin. The others are very impressed as they can only manage a double.

2.plot: Nok Tok finds a cave that makes his voice echo and is convinced he has found a new friend!

3.title: Cheebie Tune
3.plot: De Li discovers a frog in her garden which makes a very odd noise in place of a normal croak.

4.title: De Li Gets Her Shoehorns On

7.plot: Lau Lau wants to paint her narabug - but it flutters away.

9.plot: Yo Jojo hides behind a tree and talks,making Lau Lau believe that the tree is talking to her!

11.title: Dance
11.plot: Nok Tok is excitedly building a windmill extension to his Anything Machine and hoping for the wind to pick up!

12.plot: Yo Jojo wants to be able to jump as high as everyone else - but he just can't seem to manage it

13.title: The Gift

15.title: Feather
15.plot: Nok Tok is very proud of the measuring stick he's made to see how tall things have grown.

17.title: Pipling Pegs
17.plot: Yo Jojo starts a chasing game but the cheebies disappear.

18.title: No Talk Game
18.plot: As De Li rests under a plumato tree, a couple of its fruit fall.

19.title: Dry Garden
19.plot: Lau Lau has been dancing to the music produced by the pitcher plants but stops to help Yo Jojo with his project.

20.title: Carrobeet Day
20.plot: Yo Jojo is surprised when a cricket-like bug jumps out on him.

imdb.title: Waybuloo
plot: In each episode six children visit Nara to play with the Piplings and explore their land.
synopsis:
Waybuloo is not just a series, its a philosophy for a happy life, and is like nothing children will have ever seen before.
Waybuloo transports children into a magical land called Nara a real world, which is inhabited by adorable animated characters called Piplings. Taking a completely original approach, the series focuses on childrens feelings, and the Piplings embody a range of emotions including love, wisdom, happiness and harmony all in search of Waybuloo.
There are four Piplings.
Lau Lau is rabbit-like and her key characteristic is her imagination. She loves to paint and sculpt, especially if she can make presents for her friends.
Yojojo is monkey-like and represents happiness. He is clumsy, funny and cheeky. Just as Lau Lau loves to paint, Yo Jojo loves music and dancing. He even has a little stage carved from a tree stump on which to perform.
De Li is kitten-like and represents love. Shes a bit shy but is nurturing and loves nature, be it gardening, flowers or gathering food for the group.
Nok Tok is bear-like and represents wisdom. He solves problems and comes up with creative, inventive solutions for fixing and mending things. He has a very colourful toolbox and a special Anything Machine which can solve a multitude of problems.
In each episode, six children visit Nara to play with the Piplings and explore their land, as real life interacts with the animated world, showing that every child can visit Nara and find their own Waybuloo.
